%% AR Email Management — SAP UI Triggered Processing via CodeMie Orchestrator
%% Path B: SAP UI (or SAP headless) triggers on-demand email processing
%%   1. SAP UI calls CodeMie Assistants API with email message_id(s)
%%   2. CodeMie JWT authenticated via SAP PAT → PAT Gateway token exchange
%%   3. Orchestrator assistant receives message_id(s)
%%   4. Orchestrator invokes Outlook MCP tools to fetch email + thread
%%   5. Pipeline continues: ThreadSummarizer → EmailClassifier →
%%      ResponseDrafter → ActionRouter → ReviewPresenter
%%   6. Workflow enters PAUSED state (interrupt_before) for human approval
%%   7. Approved actions executed: SAP write + Outlook send
%%
%% Compare with: ar-mail-flow-ui-trigger-mcp.mermaid (Path C — delegated token)
%% Related ADRs: ADR-005 (integration pattern), ADR-006 (Path C contrast)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant SAPUI as SAP UI<br/>(Fiori / Alevate)
    participant PAT as PAT Gateway<br/>(token exchange)
    participant CM as CodeMie<br/>(Orchestrator assistant)
    participant MCP as Outlook MCP Server<br/>(app-level token)
    participant Graph as Microsoft Graph API
    participant TS as ThreadSummarizer<br/>(A2A agent)
    participant EC as EmailClassifier<br/>(A2A agent)
    participant RD as ResponseDrafter<br/>(A2A agent)
    participant AR as ActionRouter<br/>(A2A agent)
    participant RP as ReviewPresenter<br/>(A2A agent)
    participant AUD as Audit Store<br/>(PostgreSQL)
    participant SAP as SAP FS2/S4

    Note over SAPUI,PAT: Step 1 — Authentication (SAP headless path)
    SAPUI->>PAT: SAP PAT (Personal Access Token)
    PAT-->>SAPUI: CodeMie JWT (short-lived, A2A scoped)

    rect rgb(232, 244, 248)
        Note over SAPUI,CM: Step 2 — Trigger Orchestrator with email ID(s) + Graph token
        SAPUI->>CM: POST /v1/a2a/assistants/{orchestrator_id}<br/>Authorization: Bearer [codemie-jwt]<br/>X-Graph-Token: [entra-access-token]<br/>{"message_ids": ["msg-abc123"], "graph_token": "[entra-access-token]",<br/> "customer_id": "CUST-001"}
        Note over CM: X-Graph-Token identifies the user and their inbox.<br/>Stored in context store as {{graph_token}}.<br/>Without it the MCP server cannot authenticate<br/>against the correct mailbox.
        CM->>AUD: Log: trigger_source=sap_ui, message_ids=[msg-abc123],<br/>customer_id=CUST-001
    end

    rect rgb(248, 240, 232)
        Note over CM,Graph: Step 3 — Orchestrator fetches email via MCP (delegated token)
        Note over CM: Orchestrator forwards X-Graph-Token to MCP server<br/>via mcp_servers.config.headers in workflow YAML
        CM->>MCP: tool_call("get_email", {message_id: "msg-abc123"})<br/>X-Graph-Token: [entra-access-token]
        MCP->>Graph: GET /users/{mailbox}/messages/msg-abc123<br/>Authorization: Bearer [entra-access-token]<br/>Accept: application/json
        Graph-->>MCP: Email content + metadata
        MCP-->>CM: {from, subject, body, received_at, thread_id, ...}

        CM->>MCP: tool_call("get_thread", {thread_id: "thread-xyz"})<br/>X-Graph-Token: [entra-access-token]
        MCP->>Graph: GET /users/{mailbox}/messages?$filter=conversationId eq 'thread-xyz'<br/>Authorization: Bearer [entra-access-token]
        Graph-->>MCP: Thread email array
        MCP-->>CM: [{email1}, {email2}, ...] thread history

        Note over CM: Email content + thread stored in context store<br/>Keys: email, email_body, thread_emails, thread_id
    end

    rect rgb(232, 248, 232)
        Note over CM,AUD: Step 4 — AI Pipeline (A2A agent chain)
        CM->>TS: A2A: summarize thread<br/>(email + thread_emails + customer_context)
        TS-->>CM: {summary, key_facts, open_items, sentiment_trend, total_emails}
        CM->>AUD: Log: thread_summary generated

        CM->>EC: A2A: classify email<br/>(email + summary + customer_id)
        EC-->>CM: {category, sub_category, categories[], confidence,<br/>priority, intent, reasoning, extracted_data}
        CM->>AUD: Log: category, confidence, reasoning

        Note over CM: Conditional branch:<br/>ESCALATION_LEGAL / UNCLASSIFIED / AUTO_REPLY / INTERNAL_NOTE<br/>→ skip ResponseDrafter, has_draft_response=false

        alt Draft path (all other categories)
            CM->>RD: A2A: draft response<br/>(classification + thread_summary + customer_context +<br/>invoice_data + sap_template + email_body)
            RD-->>CM: {draft_subject, draft_body, tone, has_draft_response: true}
            CM->>AUD: Log: draft generated, tone, template_used
        else No-draft path
            Note over CM: draft_response=null, has_draft_response=false
        end

        CM->>AR: A2A: route actions<br/>(classification + extracted_data + has_draft_response)
        AR-->>CM: {actions[], approval_route: STANDARD|PRIORITY|SUPERVISOR|LEGAL}
        CM->>AUD: Log: actions[], approval_route

        CM->>RP: A2A: assemble review package<br/>(all pipeline outputs)
        RP-->>CM: {review_package: {header, context_section,<br/>action_section, decision_buttons, warnings}}
        CM->>AUD: Log: review_package_hash, approval_route
    end

    rect rgb(248, 232, 248)
        Note over CM,SAPUI: Step 5 — Workflow PAUSED for human approval
        Note over CM: interrupt_before=true on approval state<br/>SLA: STANDARD=4h, PRIORITY=1h,<br/>SUPERVISOR=30min, LEGAL=15min
        CM-->>SAPUI: Review package displayed in SAP/Alevate UI<br/>Decision buttons: APPROVE | EDIT_AND_APPROVE | REJECT | ESCALATE

        alt Approve
            SAPUI->>CM: Continue (approve)
            CM->>Graph: POST /users/{mailbox}/sendMail<br/>Authorization: Bearer [app-level-graph-token]<br/>(approved draft email)
            Graph-->>CM: 202 Accepted
            CM->>SAP: Execute SAP action<br/>(LOG_DISPUTE / TRIGGER_RECONCILIATION / UPDATE_SAP_DATE / LOG_EVENT)
            SAP-->>CM: Action confirmed
            CM->>AUD: Log: approved by [user-id], email sent, SAP updated

        else Edit & Approve
            SAPUI->>CM: Continue with edited draft
            CM->>Graph: POST /users/{mailbox}/sendMail (edited draft)
            Graph-->>CM: 202 Accepted
            CM->>SAP: Execute SAP action
            CM->>AUD: Log: approved with edits, diff recorded

        else Reject
            SAPUI->>CM: Cancel (reject + reason)
            CM->>AUD: Log: rejected by [user-id], reason logged<br/>Manual handling required

        else Escalate
            SAPUI->>CM: Escalate to supervisor / legal
            CM->>AUD: Log: escalated to [target], reason
        end
    end

    Note over CM,AUD: All outcomes logged with: message_id, trigger_source=sap_ui,<br/>category, approval_route, approver_id, decision, timestamp
